A recount is required by state law when there is less than a 2,000-vote margin. The recount means Washington voters will have to wait until next Wednesday to find out who their next governor is _ a stunning scenario considering the experts never thought it would be this close. ``It's fun, it's exciting, it's like a two-week playoff series. But it's a lot more important than a ballgame,'' said Joe Arko, a Texas doctor who has been following the Washington election religiously on the Internet. 